Name: MC_DIS_BREIT
Summary: MC DIS analysis for DIS kinematic observables - Breit Frame (inspired by ZEUS_2010_I875006)
Status: VALIDATED
Authors:
 - Andreas Papaefstathiou <apapaefs@kennesaw.edu> (modified)

Options:
 - JETINPUT=FULL,HARDPARTONS,TOP2PARTONS,TOP3PARTONS
 - DISMODE=NC,CC

RunInfo: Suitable for DIS.
NumEvents: 1000
PtCuts: [0]
Beams: [[p+, e-], [p+, e+]]
Description:
  Analysis of kinematic observables in DIS.
  The analysis name MC_DIS_BREIT is kept for historical continuity; the plot
  titles omit an explicit "Breit frame" label, but the jet-based observables
  are still defined using Breit-frame kinematics.
  The DIS event selection uses 49 < Q^2 < 2500 GeV^2 together with
  0.2 < y < 0.6.
  The DISMODE option defaults to NC and should be set to CC for charged-current
  ep scattering so that the DIS kinematics and Breit-frame final state are
  reconstructed with the outgoing neutrino as the scattered lepton.
  The JETINPUT option selects either the full DIS final state (FULL, default)
  only final-state q/g partons from the Rivet DIS final state (HARDPARTONS),
  the hardest 2 final-state q/g partons from the Rivet DIS final state,
  clustered in the Breit frame (TOP2PARTONS), or the hardest 3 such partons
  clustered in the Breit frame (TOP3PARTONS), as the jet inputs.
NeedsCrossSection: yes
